OpenClinica:StudyDescriptionAndStatus.OfficialTitle: Diagnostic blood test for screening of colorectal cancer (CRC) -BUPA Health Foundation Grant
OpenClinica:StudyDescriptionAndStatus.OpenClinica:DetailedDescription: CSIRO has developed a simple blood-based test that can diagnose colorectal cancer (CRC) at an early stage when the chance of cure is greater than 80%. This blood test will also significantly improve CRC screening participation and compliance in the Australian population. This study will assess the efficacy of this blood test with the current FOBT to determine if it can ultimately replace FOBT or be used as an adjunct to triage individuals for colonoscopy
OpenClinica:StudyDescriptionAndStatus.OpenClinica:Collaborators: Professor Rajvinder Singh - University of Adelaide, Mr. James Moore - Royal Adelaide Hospital, Dr. Michelle Thomas - Royal Adelaide Hospital, Professor Andrew Ruszkiewicz - University of Adelaide
